    "Domain-specific patterns fail to generalize: financial contexts show 8.8-fold higher baseline disclosure than medical contexts.• Conceptual: This work demonstrates the risk of a Reverse Gell-Mann Amnesia effect: when models appropriately disclose limitations in some professional domains, users may infer this transparency reflects principled behavior that applies broadly, creating the preconditions for misplaced trust in high-stakes contexts where disclosure fails.",
    "• Methodological: This work introduces LLM Judge Call Interweaving for efficient asynchronous evaluation achieving 56k tokens/sec on consumer hardware, and applies a novel propagation of uncertainty through a Bayesian method and Rogan-Gladen correction, modeling judge error rates as posterior distributions to demonstrate robustness across plausible measurement error ranges.",
    "Methodology Experimental DesignThe experimental design adopts a common-garden approach (Figure 1) [7], adapted from evolutionary biology's approach to decomposing phenotypic variance.",
    "All sixteen models receive identical evaluation conditions: six personas × four sequential epistemic probes × 50 replications = 19,200 total trials.",
    "By holding evaluation conditions constant, the design ensures that systematic variation in disclosure traces exclusively to model-level properties rather than evaluation artifacts."
